04984 static inline uint64_t CVMX_PCIERCX_CFG517(unsigned long offset)
04985 {
04986     switch(cvmx_get_octeon_family()) {
04987         case OCTEON_CNF75XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
04988             if ((offset <= 1))
04989                 return 0x0000020000000814ull + ((offset) & 1) * 0x100000000ull;
04990             break;
04991         case OCTEON_CN70XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
04992             if ((offset <= 2))
04993                 return 0x0000020000000814ull + ((offset) & 3) * 0x100000000ull;
04994             break;
04995         case OCTEON_CN78XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
04996             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX))
04997                 if ((offset <= 3))
04998                     return 0x0000020000000814ull + ((offset) & 3) * 0x100000000ull;
04999             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX_PASS1_X))
05000                 if ((offset <= 3))
05001                     return 0x0000020000000814ull + ((offset) & 3) * 0x100000000ull;
05002         case OCTEON_CN73XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05003             if ((offset <= 3))
05004                 return 0x0000020000000814ull + ((offset) & 3) * 0x100000000ull;
05005             break;
05006         case OCTEON_CNF71XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05007         case OCTEON_CN61XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05008         case OCTEON_CN56XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05009         case OCTEON_CN66XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05010         case OCTEON_CN52XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05011         case OCTEON_CN63XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05012         case OCTEON_CN68XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
05013             if ((offset <= 1))
05014                 return 0x0000000000000814ull;
05015             break;
05016     }
05017     cvmx_warn("CVMX_PCIERCX_CFG517 (offset = %lu) not supported on this chip\n", offset);
05018     return 0x0000020000000814ull + ((offset) & 1) * 0x100000000ull;

05825 union cvmx_pciercx_cfg015 {
05826     uint32_t u32;
05827     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg015_s {
05828 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05829     uint32_t reserved_28_31               : 4;
05830     uint32_t dtsees                       : 1;  /**< Discard timer SERR enable status. Not applicable to PCI Express, hardwired to 0. */
05831     uint32_t dts                          : 1;  /**< Discard timer status. Not applicable to PCI Express, hardwired to 0. */
05832     uint32_t sdt                          : 1;  /**< Secondary discard timer. Not applicable to PCI Express, hardwired to 0. */
05833     uint32_t pdt                          : 1;  /**< Primary discard timer. Not applicable to PCI Express, hardwired to 0. */
05834     uint32_t fbbe                         : 1;  /**< Fast back-to-back transactions enable. Not applicable to PCI Express, hardwired to 0. */
05835     uint32_t sbrst                        : 1;  /**< Secondary bus reset. Hot reset. Causes TS1s with the hot reset bit to be sent to the link
05836                                                          partner. When set, software should wait 2 ms before clearing. The link partner normally
05837                                                          responds by sending TS1s with the hot reset bit set, which will cause a link down event.

05952                                                          _ Bit 12: If set, PME Messages can be generated from D1.
05953                                                          _ Bit 13: If set, PME Messages can be generated from D2.

05961                                                          this field. */

05963                                                          application must not change this field. */

06443 /**
06444  * cvmx_pcierc#_cfg030
06445  *
06446  * This register contains the thirty-first 32-bits of PCIe type 1 configuration space.
06447  *
06448  */
06449 union cvmx_pciercx_cfg030 {
06450     uint32_t u32;
06451     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg030_s {
06452 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06453     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
06454     uint32_t tp                           : 1;  /**< Transaction pending. Hard-wired to 0. */
06455     uint32_t ap_d                         : 1;  /**< AUX power detected. Set to 1 if AUX power detected. */
06456     uint32_t ur_d                         : 1;  /**< Unsupported request detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or
06457                                                          not error reporting is enabled in the device control register. UR_D occurs when we receive
06458                                                          something unsupported. Unsupported requests are nonfatal errors, so UR_D should cause
06459                                                          NFE_D. Receiving a vendor-defined message should cause an unsupported request. */
06460     uint32_t fe_d                         : 1;  /**< Fatal error detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or not
06461                                                          error reporting is enabled in the device control register. This field is set if we receive
06462                                                          any of the errors in PCIERC()_CFG066 that has a severity set to fatal. Malformed TLPs
06463                                                          generally fit into this category. */
06464     uint32_t nfe_d                        : 1;  /**< Nonfatal error detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or not
06465                                                          error reporting is enabled in the device control register. This field is set if we receive
06466                                                          any of the errors in PCIERC()_CFG066 that has a severity set to Nonfatal and does NOT
06467                                                          meet Advisory Nonfatal criteria, which most poisoned TLPs should. */
06468     uint32_t ce_d                         : 1;  /**< Correctable error detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or
06469                                                          not error reporting is enabled in the device control register. This field is set if we
06470                                                          receive any of the errors in PCIERC()_CFG068, for example, a replay timer timeout.
06471                                                          Also, it can be set if we get any of the errors in PCIERC()_CFG066 that has a severity
06472                                                          set to nonfatal and meets the advisory nonfatal criteria, which most ECRC errors should. */
06473     uint32_t reserved_15_15               : 1;
06474     uint32_t mrrs                         : 3;  /**< Max read request size.
06475                                                          0x0 =128 bytes.
06476                                                          0x1 = 256 bytes.
06477                                                          0x2 = 512 bytes.
06478                                                          0x3 = 1024 bytes.
06479                                                          0x4 = 2048 bytes.
06480                                                          0x5 = 4096 bytes.
06481                                                          SLI_S2M_PORT()_CTL[MRRS] and DPI_SLI_PRT()_CFG[MRRS] must also be set properly.
06482                                                          SLI_S2M_PORT()_CTL[MRRS] and DPI_SLI_PRT()_CFG[MRRS] must not exceed the desired
06483                                                          max read request size. */
06484     uint32_t ns_en                        : 1;  /**< Enable no snoop. */
06485     uint32_t ap_en                        : 1;  /**< AUX power PM enable (not supported). */
06486     uint32_t pf_en                        : 1;  /**< Phantom function enable. This bit should never be set; CNXXXX requests never use phantom functions. */
06487     uint32_t etf_en                       : 1;  /**< Extended tag field enable. Set this bit to enable extended tags. */
06488     uint32_t mps                          : 3;  /**< Max payload size. Legal values: 0x0 = 128 B, 0x1 = 256 B.
06489                                                          Larger sizes are not supported.
06490                                                          Both PCI Express ports must be set to the same value for peer-to-peer to function
06491                                                          properly.
06492                                                          DPI_SLI_PRT()_CFG[MPS] must be set to the same value as this field for proper
06493                                                          functionality. */
06494     uint32_t ro_en                        : 1;  /**< Enable relaxed ordering. */
06495     uint32_t ur_en                        : 1;  /**< Unsupported request reporting enable. */
06496     uint32_t fe_en                        : 1;  /**< Fatal error reporting enable. */
06497     uint32_t nfe_en                       : 1;  /**< Nonfatal error reporting enable. */
06498     uint32_t ce_en                        : 1;  /**< Correctable error reporting enable. */
06499 #else
06500     uint32_t ce_en                        : 1;
06501     uint32_t nfe_en                       : 1;
06502     uint32_t fe_en                        : 1;
06503     uint32_t ur_en                        : 1;
06504     uint32_t ro_en                        : 1;
06505     uint32_t mps                          : 3;
06506     uint32_t etf_en                       : 1;
06507     uint32_t pf_en                        : 1;
06508     uint32_t ap_en                        : 1;
06509     uint32_t ns_en                        : 1;
06510     uint32_t mrrs                         : 3;
06511     uint32_t reserved_15_15               : 1;
06512     uint32_t ce_d                         : 1;
06513     uint32_t nfe_d                        : 1;
06514     uint32_t fe_d                         : 1;
06515     uint32_t ur_d                         : 1;
06516     uint32_t ap_d                         : 1;
06517     uint32_t tp                           : 1;
06518     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
06519 #endif
06520     } s;

06522     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg030_s          cn52xxp1;
06523     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg030_s          cn56xx;
06524     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg030_s          cn56xxp1;

06576                                                          PEM()_CFG[MD].
06577                                                          _ MD is 0x0, reset to 0x1: 2.5 GHz supported.
06578                                                          _ MD is 0x1, reset to 0x2: 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
06579                                                          _ MD is 0x2, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
06580                                                          _ MD is 0x3, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported (RC Mode).
06581                                                          This field is writable through PEM()_CFG_WR. However, the application must not change
06582                                                          this field. */

06590     uint32_t sderc                        : 1;

06668 /**
06669  * cvmx_pcierc#_cfg032
06670  *
06671  * This register contains the thirty-third 32-bits of PCIe type 1 configuration space.
06672  *
06673  */
06674 union cvmx_pciercx_cfg032 {
06675     uint32_t u32;
06676     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg032_s {
06677 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06678     uint32_t lab                          : 1;  /**< Link autonomous bandwidth status. This bit is set to indicate that hardware has
06679                                                          autonomously changed link speed or width, without the port transitioning through DL_Down
06680                                                          status, for reasons other than to attempt to correct unreliable link operation. */
06681     uint32_t lbm                          : 1;  /**< Link bandwidth management status. This bit is set to indicate either of the following has
06682                                                          occurred without the port transitioning through DL_DOWN status:
06683                                                          * A link retraining has completed following a write of 1b to the retrain link bit.
06684                                                          * Hardware has changed the Link speed or width to attempt to correct unreliable link
06685                                                          operation, either through a LTSSM timeout of higher level process. This bit must be set if
06686                                                          the physical layer reports a speed or width change was initiated by the downstream
06687                                                          component that was not indicated as an autonomous change. */
06688     uint32_t dlla                         : 1;  /**< Data link layer active. */
06689     uint32_t scc                          : 1;  /**< Slot clock configuration. Indicates that the component uses the same physical reference
06690                                                          clock that the platform provides on the connector. The default value is the value you
06691                                                          select during hardware configuration, writable through PEM()_CFG_WR. However, the
06692                                                          application must not change this field. */
06693     uint32_t lt                           : 1;  /**< Link training. */
06694     uint32_t reserved_26_26               : 1;
06695     uint32_t nlw                          : 6;  /**< Negotiated link width. Set automatically by hardware after link initialization. Value is
06696                                                          undefined when link is not up. */
06697     uint32_t ls                           : 4;  /**< Current link speed. The encoded value specifies a bit location in the supported link
06698                                                          speeds vector (in the link capabilities 2 register) that corresponds to the current link
06699                                                          speed.
06700                                                          0x1 = Supported link speeds vector field bit 0.
06701                                                          0x2 = Supported link speeds vector field bit 1.
06702                                                          0x3 = Supported link speeds vector field bit 2. */

06705                                                          interrupt to indicate that the link autonomous bandwidth status bit has been set. */
06706     uint32_t lbm_int_enb                  : 1;  /**< Link bandwidth management interrupt enable. When set, enables the generation of an
06707                                                          interrupt to indicate that the link bandwidth management status bit has been set. */
06708     uint32_t hawd                         : 1;  /**< Hardware autonomous width disable (not supported). */
06709     uint32_t ecpm                         : 1;  /**< Enable clock power management. Hardwired to 0 if clock power management is disabled in the
06710                                                          link capabilities register. */
06711     uint32_t es                           : 1;  /**< Extended synch. */
06712     uint32_t ccc                          : 1;  /**< Common clock configuration. */
06713     uint32_t rl                           : 1;  /**< Retrain link. */
06714     uint32_t ld                           : 1;  /**< Link disable. */
06715     uint32_t rcb                          : 1;  /**< Read completion boundary (RCB), writable through
06716                                                          PEM()_CFG_WR. However, the application must not change this field because an RCB of 64
06717                                                          bytes is not supported. */
06718     uint32_t reserved_2_2                 : 1;
06719     uint32_t aslpc                        : 2;  /**< Active state link PM control. */
06720 #else
06721     uint32_t aslpc                        : 2;
06722     uint32_t reserved_2_2                 : 1;
06723     uint32_t rcb                          : 1;
06724     uint32_t ld                           : 1;
06725     uint32_t rl                           : 1;
06726     uint32_t ccc                          : 1;
06727     uint32_t es                           : 1;
06728     uint32_t ecpm                         : 1;

06731     uint32_t lab_int_enb                  : 1;

06734     uint32_t nlw                          : 6;

06739     uint32_t lbm                          : 1;
06740     uint32_t lab                          : 1;

07405                                                          For each bit, a value of 1 b indicates that the corresponding link speed is supported;
07406                                                          otherwise, the link speed is not supported. Bit definitions are:
07407                                                          _ Bit <1> = 2.5 GT/s.

07413                                                          _ MD is 0x1, reset to 0x3: 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
07414                                                          _ MD is 0x2, reset to 0x7: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
07415                                                          _ MD is 0x3, reset to 0x7: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported (RC Mode). */
07416     uint32_t reserved_0_0                 : 1;
07417 #else

07450 /**
07451  * cvmx_pcierc#_cfg040
07452  *
07453  * This register contains the forty-first 32-bits of PCIe type 1 configuration space.
07454  *
07455  */
07456 union cvmx_pciercx_cfg040 {
07457     uint32_t u32;
07458     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_s {
07459 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
07460     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
07461     uint32_t ler                          : 1;  /**< Link equalization request */
07462     uint32_t ep3s                         : 1;  /**< Equalization phase 3 successful */
07463     uint32_t ep2s                         : 1;  /**< Equalization phase 2 successful */
07464     uint32_t ep1s                         : 1;  /**< Equalization phase 1 successful */
07465     uint32_t eqc                          : 1;  /**< Equalization complete */
07466     uint32_t cdl                          : 1;  /**< Current deemphasis level. When the link is operating at 5 GT/s speed, this bit reflects
07467                                                          the level of deemphasis. Encodings:
07468                                                          1 = -3.5 dB.
07469                                                          0 = -6 dB.
07470                                                          The value in this bit is undefined when the link is operating at 2.5 GT/s speed. */
07471     uint32_t cde                          : 4;  /**< Compliance deemphasis. This bit sets the deemphasis level in Polling.Compliance state if
07472                                                          the entry occurred due to the TX compliance receive bit being 1. Encodings:
07473                                                          0x1 = -3.5 dB.
07474                                                          0x0 = -6 dB.
07475                                                          When the Link is operating at 2.5 GT/s, the setting of this bit has no effect. */
07476     uint32_t csos                         : 1;  /**< Compliance SOS. When set to 1, the LTSSM is required to send SKP ordered sets periodically
07477                                                          in between the (modified) compliance patterns.
07478                                                          When the link is operating at 2.5 GT/s, the setting of this bit has no effect. */
07479     uint32_t emc                          : 1;  /**< Enter modified compliance. When this bit is set to 1, the device transmits a modified
07480                                                          compliance pattern if the LTSSM enters Polling.Compliance state. */
07481     uint32_t tm                           : 3;  /**< Transmit margin. This field controls the value of the non-deemphasized voltage level at
07482                                                          the transmitter signals:
07483                                                          0x0 =  800-1200 mV for full swing 400-600 mV for half-swing.
07484                                                          0x1-0x2 = Values must be monotonic with a nonzero slope.
07485                                                          0x3 = 200-400 mV for full-swing and 100-200 mV for half-swing.
07486                                                          0x4-0x7 = Reserved.
07487                                                          This field is reset to 0x0 on entry to the LTSSM Polling.Compliance substate. When
07488                                                          operating in 5.0 GT/s mode with full swing, the deemphasis ratio must be maintained within
07489                                                          +/- 1 dB from the specification-defined operational value either -3.5 or -6 dB. */
07490     uint32_t sde                          : 1;  /**< Selectable deemphasis. When the link is operating at 5.0 GT/s speed, selects the level of
07491                                                          deemphasis on the downstream device.  Must be set prior to link training.
07492                                                          1 = -3.5 dB.
07493                                                          0 = -6 dB.
07494                                                          When the link is operating at 2.5 GT/s speed, the setting of this bit has no effect.
07495                                                          PCIERC()_CFG515[S_D_E] can be used to change the deemphasis on the upstream ports. */
07496     uint32_t hasd                         : 1;  /**< Hardware autonomous speed disable. When asserted, the application must disable hardware
07497                                                          from changing the link speed for device-specific reasons other than attempting to correct
07498                                                          unreliable link operation by reducing link speed. Initial transition to the highest
07499                                                          supported common link speed is not blocked by this signal. */
07500     uint32_t ec                           : 1;  /**< Enter compliance. Software is permitted to force a link to enter compliance mode at the
07501                                                          speed indicated in the target link speed field by setting this bit to 1 in both components
07502                                                          on a link and then initiating a hot reset on the link. */
07503     uint32_t tls                          : 4;  /**< Target link speed. For downstream ports, this field sets an upper limit on link
07504                                                          operational speed by restricting the values advertised by the upstream component in its
07505                                                          training sequences:
07506                                                          0x1 = 2.5 Gb/s target link speed.
07507                                                          0x2 = 5 Gb/s target link speed.
07508                                                          0x3 = 8 Gb/s target link speed.
07509                                                          All other encodings are reserved.
07510                                                          If a value is written to this field that does not correspond to a speed included in the
07511                                                          supported link speeds field, the result is undefined. For both upstream and downstream
07512                                                          ports, this field is used to set the target compliance mode speed when software is using
07513                                                          the enter compliance bit to force a link into compliance mode.
07514                                                          The reset value of this field is controlled by the value read from PEM()_CFG[MD].
07515                                                          _ MD is 0x0, reset to 0x1: 2.5 GHz supported.
07516                                                          _ MD is 0x1, reset to 0x2: 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
07517                                                          _ MD is 0x2, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
07518                                                          _ MD is 0x3, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported (RC Mode). */
07519 #else
07520     uint32_t tls                          : 4;
07521     uint32_t ec                           : 1;
07522     uint32_t hasd                         : 1;
07523     uint32_t sde                          : 1;
07524     uint32_t tm                           : 3;
07525     uint32_t emc                          : 1;
07526     uint32_t csos                         : 1;
07527     uint32_t cde                          : 4;
07528     uint32_t cdl                          : 1;
07529     uint32_t eqc                          : 1;
07530     uint32_t ep1s                         : 1;
07531     uint32_t ep2s                         : 1;
07532     uint32_t ep3s                         : 1;
07533     uint32_t ler                          : 1;
07534     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
07535 #endif
07536     } s;
07537     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn52xx {
07538 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
07539     uint32_t reserved_0_31                : 32;
07540 #else
07541     uint32_t reserved_0_31                : 32;
07542 #endif
07543     } cn52xx;
07544     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn52xx     cn52xxp1;
07545     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn52xx     cn56xx;
07546     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn52xx     cn56xxp1;
07547     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx {
07548 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
07549     uint32_t reserved_17_31               : 15;
07550     uint32_t cdl                          : 1;  /**< Current De-emphasis Level
07551                                                          When the Link is operating at 5 GT/s speed, this bit
07552                                                          reflects the level of de-emphasis. Encodings:
07553                                                           1b: -3.5 dB
07554                                                           0b: -6 dB
07555                                                          Note: The value in this bit is undefined when the Link is
07556                                                          operating at 2.5 GT/s speed */
07557     uint32_t reserved_13_15               : 3;
07558     uint32_t cde                          : 1;  /**< Compliance De-emphasis
07559                                                          This bit sets the de-emphasis level in Polling. Compliance
07560                                                          state if the entry occurred due to the Tx Compliance
07561                                                          Receive bit being 1b. Encodings:
07562                                                           1b: -3.5 dB
07563                                                           0b: -6 dB
07564                                                          Note: When the Link is operating at 2.5 GT/s, the setting
07565                                                          of this bit has no effect. */
07566     uint32_t csos                         : 1;  /**< Compliance SOS
07567                                                          When set to 1b, the LTSSM is required to send SKP
07568                                                          Ordered Sets periodically in between the (modified)
07569                                                          compliance patterns.
07570                                                          Note: When the Link is operating at 2.5 GT/s, the setting
07571                                                          of this bit has no effect. */
07572     uint32_t emc                          : 1;  /**< Enter Modified Compliance
07573                                                          When this bit is set to 1b, the device transmits a modified
07574                                                          compliance pattern if the LTSSM enters Polling.
07575                                                          Compliance state. */
07576     uint32_t tm                           : 3;  /**< Transmit Margin
07577                                                          This field controls the value of the non-de-emphasized
07578                                                          voltage level at the Transmitter pins:
07579                                                           - 000: 800-1200 mV for full swing 400-600 mV for half-swing
07580                                                           - 001-010: values must be monotonic with a non-zero slope
07581                                                           - 011: 200-400 mV for full-swing and 100-200 mV for halfswing
07582                                                           - 100-111: reserved
07583                                                          This field is reset to 000b on entry to the LTSSM Polling.
07584                                                          Compliance substate.
07585                                                          When operating in 5.0 GT/s mode with full swing, the
07586                                                          de-emphasis ratio must be maintained within +/- 1 dB
07587                                                          from the specification-defined operational value
07588                                                          either -3.5 or -6 dB). */
07589     uint32_t sde                          : 1;  /**< Selectable De-emphasis
07590                                                          When the Link is operating at 5.0 GT/s speed, selects the
07591                                                          level of de-emphasis:
07592                                                          - 1: -3.5 dB
07593                                                          - 0: -6 dB
07594                                                          When the Link is operating at 2.5 GT/s speed, the setting
07595                                                          of this bit has no effect. */
07596     uint32_t hasd                         : 1;  /**< Hardware Autonomous Speed Disable
07597                                                          When asserted, the
07598                                                          application must disable hardware from changing the Link
07599                                                          speed for device-specific reasons other than attempting to
07600                                                          correct unreliable Link operation by reducing Link speed.
07601                                                          Initial transition to the highest supported common link
07602                                                          speed is not blocked by this signal. */
07603     uint32_t ec                           : 1;  /**< Enter Compliance
07604                                                          Software is permitted to force a link to enter Compliance
07605                                                          mode at the speed indicated in the Target Link Speed
07606                                                          field by setting this bit to 1b in both components on a link
07607                                                          and then initiating a hot reset on the link. */
07608     uint32_t tls                          : 4;  /**< Target Link Speed
07609                                                          For Downstream ports, this field sets an upper limit on link
07610                                                          operational speed by restricting the values advertised by
07611                                                          the upstream component in its training sequences:
07612                                                            - 0001: 2.5Gb/s Target Link Speed
07613                                                            - 0010: 5Gb/s Target Link Speed
07614                                                            - 0100: 8Gb/s Target Link Speed (Not Supported)
07615                                                          All other encodings are reserved.
07616                                                          If a value is written to this field that does not correspond to
07617                                                          a speed included in the Supported Link Speeds field, the
07618                                                          result is undefined.
07619                                                          For both Upstream and Downstream ports, this field is
07620                                                          used to set the target compliance mode speed when
07621                                                          software is using the Enter Compliance bit to force a link
07622                                                          into compliance mode.
07623                                                          The reset value of this field is controlled by a value sent from
07624                                                          the lsb of the MIO_QLM#_SPD register.
07625                                                          qlm#_spd[0]   RST_VALUE   NOTE
07626                                                          1             0001b       2.5 GHz supported
07627                                                          0             0010b       5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported */
07628 #else
07629     uint32_t tls                          : 4;
07630     uint32_t ec                           : 1;
07631     uint32_t hasd                         : 1;
07632     uint32_t sde                          : 1;
07633     uint32_t tm                           : 3;
07634     uint32_t emc                          : 1;
07635     uint32_t csos                         : 1;
07636     uint32_t cde                          : 1;
07637     uint32_t reserved_13_15               : 3;
07638     uint32_t cdl                          : 1;
07639     uint32_t reserved_17_31               : 15;
07640 #endif
07641     } cn61xx;
07642     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cn63xx;
07643     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cn63xxp1;
07644     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cn66xx;
07645     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cn68xx;
07646     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cn68xxp1;
07647     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cn70xx;
07648     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cn70xxp1;
07649     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_s          cn73xx;
07650     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_s          cn78xx;

07652     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg040_cn61xx     cnf71xx;

09635 /**
09636  * cvmx_pcierc#_cfg452
09637  *
09638  * This register contains the four hundred fifty-third 32-bits of PCIe type 1 configuration space.
09639  *
09640  */
09641 union cvmx_pciercx_cfg452 {
09642     uint32_t u32;
09643     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg452_s {
09644 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
09645     uint32_t reserved_26_31               : 6;
09646     uint32_t eccrc                        : 1;  /**< Enable Corrupted CRC
09647                                                          Causes corrupt LCRC for TLPs when set,
09648                                                          using the pattern contained in the Other Message register.
09649                                                          This is a test feature, not to be used in normal operation. */
09650     uint32_t reserved_22_24               : 3;
09651     uint32_t lme                          : 6;  /**< Link mode enable set as follows:
09652                                                          0x1 = x1.
09653                                                          0x3 = x2.
09654                                                          0x7 = x4.
09655                                                          0xF = x8   (not supported).
09656                                                          0x1F = x16 (not supported).
09657                                                          0x3F = x32 (not supported).
09658                                                          This field indicates the maximum number of lanes supported by the PCIe port. The value can
09659                                                          be set less than 0xF to limit the number of lanes the PCIe will attempt to use. The
09660                                                          programming of this field needs to be done by software before enabling the link. See also
09661                                                          PCIERC()_CFG031[MLW].
09662                                                          The value of this field does not indicate the number of lanes in use by the PCIe. This
09663                                                          field sets the maximum number of lanes in the PCIe core that could be used. As per the
09664                                                          PCIe specification, the PCIe core can negotiate a smaller link width, so all of x8, x4,
09665                                                          x2, and x1 are supported when
09666                                                          LME = 0xF, for example. */
09667     uint32_t reserved_12_15               : 4;
09668     uint32_t link_rate                    : 4;  /**< Reserved. */
09669     uint32_t flm                          : 1;  /**< Fast link mode. Sets all internal timers to fast mode for simulation purposes. */
09670     uint32_t reserved_6_6                 : 1;
09671     uint32_t dllle                        : 1;  /**< DLL link enable. Enables link initialization. If DLL link enable = 0, the PCI Express bus
09672                                                          does not transmit InitFC DLLPs and does not establish a link. */
09673     uint32_t reserved_4_4                 : 1;
09674     uint32_t ra                           : 1;  /**< Reset assert. Triggers a recovery and forces the LTSSM to the hot reset state (downstream
09675                                                          port only). */
09676     uint32_t le                           : 1;  /**< Loopback enable. Initiate loopback mode as a master. On a 0->1 transition, the PCIe core
09677                                                          sends TS ordered sets with the loopback bit set to cause the link partner to enter into
09678                                                          loopback mode as a slave. Normal transmission is not possible when LE=1. To exit loopback
09679                                                          mode, take the link through a reset sequence. */

09682                                                          the message contained in the other message register. */

09700     struct cvmx_pciercx_cfg452_cn52xx {

09704                                                          Causes corrupt LCRC for TLPs when set,
09705                                                          using the pattern contained in the Other Message register.
09706                                                          This is a test feature, not to be used in normal operation. */
09707     uint32_t reserved_22_24               : 3;
09708     uint32_t lme                          : 6;  /**< Link Mode Enable
09709                                                          o 000001: x1
09710                                                          o 000011: x2
09711                                                          o 000111: x4
09712                                                          o 001111: x8 (not supported)
09713                                                          o 011111: x16 (not supported)
09714                                                          o 111111: x32 (not supported)
09715                                                          This field indicates the MAXIMUM number of lanes supported
09716                                                          by the PCIe port. It is normally set to 0x7 or 0x3 depending
09717                                                          on the value of the QLM_CFG bits (0x7 when QLM_CFG == 0x3
09718                                                          otherwise 0x3). The value can be set less than 0x7 or 0x3
09719                                                          to limit the number of lanes the PCIe will attempt to use.
09720                                                          The programming of this field needs to be done by SW BEFORE
09721                                                          enabling the link. See also MLW.
09722                                                          (Note: The value of this field does NOT indicate the number
09723                                                           of lanes in use by the PCIe. LME sets the max number of lanes
09724                                                           in the PCIe core that COULD be used. As per the PCIe specs,
09725                                                           the PCIe core can negotiate a smaller link width, so all
09726                                                           of x4, x2, and x1 are supported when LME=0x7,
09727                                                           for example.) */
09728     uint32_t reserved_8_15                : 8;
09729     uint32_t flm                          : 1;  /**< Fast Link Mode
09730                                                          Sets all internal timers to fast mode for simulation purposes. */

09750                                                          transmits the Message contained in the Other Message register. */

10891                                                          link width to ignore broken lanes that detect a receiver, but will not exit electrical
10892                                                          idle and would otherwise prevent a valid link from being configured. */
10893     uint32_t n_fts                        : 8;  /**< N_FTS. Sets the number of fast training sequences (N_FTS) that the core advertises as its

10895                                                          PHY's ability to recover synchronization after a low power state.
10896                                                          Do not set [N_FTS] to zero; doing so can cause the LTSSM to go into the recovery state
10897                                                          when

11069                                                          _ 0b0000000000000000 = No preset req/evaluated in EQ master phase.

11081                                                          _ All other encodings = Reserved. */

11084                                                          the PHY does not respond within 2 ms to the assertion of RxEqEval:
11085                                                          0 = Abort the current evaluation; stop any attempt to modify the remote transmitter
11086                                                          settings. Phase2 will be terminated by the 24 ms timeout.
11087                                                          1 = Ignore the 2 ms timeout and continue as normal. This is used to support PHYs that
11088                                                          require more than 2 ms to respond to the assertion of RxEqEval. */
11089     uint32_t bt                           : 1;  /**< Behavior after 24 ms timeout (when optimal settings are not found).
11090                                                          For a USP: determine the next LTSSM state from Phase2:
11091                                                          0 = Recovery.Speed.
11092                                                          1 = Recovry.Equalization.Phase3.
11093                                                          For a DSP: determine the next LTSSM state from Phase3:
11094                                                          0 = Recovery.Speed.
11095                                                          1 = Recovry.Equalization.RcrLock.
11096                                                          When optimal settings are not found:
11097                                                          * Equalization phase 3 successful status bit is not set in the link status register.
11098                                                          * Equalization phase 3 complete status bit is set in the link status register. */
11099     uint32_t fm                           : 4;  /**< Feedback mode.
11100                                                          0 = Direction of change (not supported).
11101                                                          1 = Figure of merit.
11102                                                          2-15 = Reserved. */
